formulas.formula:
Here is the complete formula sheet for CBSE Class 11 Economics - Measures of Dispersion in JSON format:

```json
[
  {
    "name": "Range",
    "formula": "R = X_max - X_min",
    "variables": {
      "R": "Range",
      "X_max": "Maximum value of the data set",
      "X_min": "Minimum value of the data set"
    },
    "units": "Same as data",
    "notes": "Simple and easy to calculate, but not suitable for large data sets."
  },
  {
    "name": "Mean Deviation (MD)",
    "formula": "MD = (1/n) \* Σ |Xi - X̄|",
    "variables": {
      "MD": "Mean Deviation",
      "n": "Number of observations",
      "Xi": "Individual data points",
      "X̄": "Mean of the data set"
    },
    "units": "Same as data",
    "notes": "Suitable for small data sets, but not suitable for large data sets."
  },
  {
    "name": "Variance (σ^2)",
    "formula": "σ^2 = (1/(n-1)) \* Σ (Xi - X̄)^2",
    "variables": {
      "σ^2": "Variance",
      "n": "Number of observations",
      "Xi": "Individual data points",
      "X̄": "Mean of the data set"
    },
    "units": "Square of the unit of data",
    "notes": "Suitable for large data sets, but not suitable for small data sets."
  },
  {
    "name": "Standard Deviation (σ)",
    "formula": "σ = √σ^2",
    "variables": {
      "σ": "Standard Deviation",
      "σ^2": "Variance"
    },
    "units": "Unit of data",
    "notes": "A measure of spread that is easily interpretable."
  },
  {
    "name": "Quartile Deviation (QD)",
    "formula": "QD = (Q3 - Q1)/2",
    "variables": {
      "QD": "Quartile Deviation",
      "Q3": "Third quartile",
      "Q1": "First quartile"
    },
    "units": "Same as data",
    "notes": "Suitable for skewed distributions."
  },
  {
    "name": "Interquartile Range (IQR)",
    "formula": "IQR = Q3 - Q1",
    "variables": {
      "IQR": "Interquartile Range",
      "Q3": "Third quartile",
      "Q1": "First quartile"
    },
    "units": "Same as data",
    "notes": "A measure of spread that is easily interpretable."
  }
]
```

Note: This list includes only the most commonly used measures of dispersion.
